item.title: Compile help!
item.dc:creator: @lothy Lothy
item.description:
@lothy wrote:

Will everyone get over Mod Taharok’s compiler, and actually go out of your way to just learn how compiling and running Java works? What happens if you go somewhere and you need to compile and run a Java program, but you don’t have internet access? Seriously.

Google setting your classpaths. If you don’t feel comfortable changing those, then find out the version of your JDK and modify the version by vraj to fit your own needs.
